  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study investigates if reduced serum levels of vitamin D concentration are a typical
      feature in patient group with low left ventricular function admitted for cardiac surgery
      interventions. and also the necessity of more preventive strategies for adequate nutrition of
      these patients with more focus on intake of vitamin D before admission to cardiac surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
